{"sha": "ae4e1a190be74024997551d2fe8c183866fc1cc5", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmFlNGUxYTE5MGJlNzQwMjQ5OTc1NTFkMmZlOGMxODM4NjZmYzFjYzU=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Huon Wilson", "email": "dbau.pp+github@gmail.com", "date": "2015-01-24T23:28:58Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Huon Wilson", "email": "dbau.pp+github@gmail.com", "date": "2015-01-24T23:44:56Z"}, "message": "Tell the compiler to tell us that `deriving` is dead.\n\nI'm beginning to suspect it's impossible to avoid accidentally writing\n`#[deriving]` at least once in every program, and it results in\nnon-intuitive error messages: \"Foo doesn't have any method in scope\n`clone`\" despite there being a `#[deriv...(Clone)]` attribute!\n\nAlso, lots of documentation around the internet uses `#[deriving]` so\nproviding this guidance is very helpful (lots of people ask in #rust\nabout this error).\n\nFixes #21166.", "tree": {"sha": "40771e090f7cd92a9dd0a6f10a9abf6d3d37e139", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/40771e090f7cd92a9dd0a6f10a9abf6d3d37e139"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/ae4e1a190be74024997551d2fe8c183866fc1cc5", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/ae4e1a190be74024997551d2fe8c183866fc1cc5", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/ae4e1a190be74024997551d2fe8c183866fc1cc5", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/ae4e1a190be74024997551d2fe8c183866fc1cc5/comments", "author": {"login": "huonw", "id": 1203825, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDM4MjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1203825?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/huonw", "html_url": "https://github.com/huonw", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huonw/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/huonw/following{/other_user}", "gists_u